{"id":1245888218,"question_id":2,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"1 month, 1 week","timestamp":1714497847,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"50 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1245888218/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"16.6 MB","code":"# Definition for singly-linked list.\n# class ListNode:\n#     def __init__(self, val=0, next=None):\n#         self.val = val\n#         self.next = next\nclass Solution:\n    def join_list(self, l1: Optional[ListNode]) -> int:\n        num_str = ''\n        while l1 != None:\n            num_str += str(l1.val)\n            l1 = l1.next\n        return int(num_str[::-1])\n\n    def addTwoNumbers(self, l1: Optional[ListNode], l2: Optional[ListNode]) -> Optional[ListNode]:\n        added_nums = str(self.join_list(l1) + self.join_list(l2))[::-1]\n        if len(added_nums) == 0: return ListNode()\n        elif len(added_nums) == 1: return ListNode(int(added_nums))\n        \n        head = ListNode(val=added_nums[0])\n        next_node = ListNode(val=added_nums[1])\n        head.next = next_node\n        if len(added_nums) == 2: return head\n        \n        for digit in added_nums[2:]:\n            next_node.next = ListNode(val=digit)\n            next_node = next_node.next\n        return head","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
